segment.source: This error indicates one of two situations, low memory resources or Windows Firewall group policy registry corruption.
segment.target: This error indicates one of two situations, low memory resources or Windows Firewall group policy registry corruption.

segment.source: Typically if this event occurs it indicates that Windows Firewall service was not able to start.
segment.target: Typically if this event occurs it indicates that Windows Firewall service was not able to start.

segment.source: It typically occurs with “5027(S): The Windows Firewall Service was unable to retrieve the security policy from the local storage.
segment.target: It typically occurs with “5027(S): The Windows Firewall Service was unable to retrieve the security policy from the local storage.

segment.source: The service will continue enforcing the current policy.”
segment.target: The service will continue enforcing the current policy.”
